stepTitle: A firework rocket is shot upward at a rate of 640 $$\frac{ft}{sec}$$. Use the projectile formula h $$=$$ $$-16t^2$$ + vt to determine when the height of the firework rocket will be 1200 feet.
stepBody: Please enter your answer as a real number without a unit. If there is more than one answer, please enter it as (a,b) where $$a<b$$.
